main event: A series of UFO sightings reported from Auburn, Washington, likely attributed to the Cosmos 103 rocket body.
interesting points: The sightings occurred between June 28 and July 2, 1963., The sightings were of a moving star-like object., Space Defense Center engineers evaluated the sightings to determine visibility of the Cosmos 103 rocket body., The Air Force concluded that the rocket body was the probable cause of the sightings., A memo indicated that the story was affecting Air Force public perception.
sighted object: a moving star-like point-source of light
witness description: The document does not specify the number of witnesses or descriptions.
